<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
Seven species of 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Cercospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cercospora" order="Mycosphaerellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Cercospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have previously been recorded on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vigna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vigna" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Vigna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 4" captionStartId="T4" captionText="Table 4. Comparison of Cercospora rhynchophora (YMM 03 B) on Vigna unguiculata, Cercospora tentaculifera (YMM 75) on Vigna unguiculata as well as on Phaseolus vulgaris and C. vignae-subterraneae (YMM 293, see below) on Vigna subterranea with Cercospora species known from Vigna spp. based on literature a-f." pageId="0" pageNumber="69">4</tableCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Farr, DF" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Genetics and Cytology" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" publicationUrl="https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" refId="B54" refString="Farr, DF, Rossman, AY, 2021. Fungal Databases, U.S. National Fungus Collections, ARS, USDA. https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" title="Fungal Databases, U. S. National Fungus Collections, ARS, USDA." url="https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" year="2021">Farr and Rossman 2021</bibRefCitation>
). However, no species of 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Cercospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cercospora" order="Mycosphaerellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Cercospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vigna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vigna subterranea" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Vigna subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Farr, DF" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Genetics and Cytology" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" publicationUrl="https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" refId="B54" refString="Farr, DF, Rossman, AY, 2021. Fungal Databases, U.S. National Fungus Collections, ARS, USDA. https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" title="Fungal Databases, U. S. National Fungus Collections, ARS, USDA." url="https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" year="2021">Farr and Rossman 2021</bibRefCitation>
), a plant species native to West Africa and cultivated mainly in the warm tropics of sub-Saharan Africa (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114681" author="Hepper, FN" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="395 - 407" refId="B69" refString="Hepper, FN, 1963. Plants of the 1957-58 West African expedition: II. The Bambara Groundnut (Voandzeia subterranea) and Kersting's Groundnut (Kerstingiella geocarpa) wild in West Africa. Kew Bulletin 16: 395 - 407, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114681" title="Plants of the 1957 - 58 West African expedition: II. The Bambara Groundnut (Voandzeia subterranea) and Kersting's Groundnut (Kerstingiella geocarpa) wild in West Africa." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114681" volume="16" year="1963">Hepper 1963</bibRefCitation>
). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. vignae-subterraneae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vignae-subterraneae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">C. vignae-subterraneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from all seven species of 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Cercospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cercospora" order="Mycosphaerellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Cercospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned above (Table 
